  "prompt": "What's so special about Tamil writer Jayakanthan's novels?",
  "response": "Jayakanthan (1934-2015) was a renowned Tamil writer known for his unique literary style and social commentary. Some notable aspects of his novels include:\n\n1. Social Realism\n- Portrayed realistic characters from working-class and marginalized backgrounds\n- Highlighted social issues like gender inequality, caste discrimination, and urban poverty\n\n2. Progressive Themes\n- Challenged traditional social norms\n- Wrote about women's empowerment and individual freedom\n- Explored complex psychological dimensions of characters\n\n3. Writing Style\n- Simple, direct narrative style\n- Conversational and engaging language\n- Used subtle humor and irony in storytelling\n\n4. Psychological Depth\n- Explored inner conflicts and emotional landscapes of characters\n- Focused on nuanced character development\n- Analyzed human psychology with sensitivity\n\n5. Literary Recognition\n- Received Sahitya Akademi Award\n- Padma Bhushan recipient\n- Considered a significant figure in modern Tamil literature\n\n6. Diverse Writing\n- Wrote novels, short stories, and screenplays\n- Worked across multiple genres\n- Known for both fiction and non-fiction writing\n\nJayakanthan was respected for his progressive outlook and ability to capture social complexities through compelling storytelling.",
